<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The controlling expression if (MHD_NO != MHD_is_feature_supported(MHD_FEATURE_POLL)) is effectively invariant for a given build because MHD_is_feature_supported(MHD_FEATURE_POLL) returns MHD_YES or MHD_NO based solely on preprocessor configuration (e.g. HAVE_POLL). The condition is therefore a constant at runtime (not an infinite loop nor a permitted do-while constant-false case), so it violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.3.
</scenario>
